# Pull request description style

When creating a PR (`gh pr create`) for this repo, use this structure exactly:

## Title

One imperative line: what the change does and where (e.g. `Bundle workflow input assets and harden ComfyUI CI failure handling`).

## Body

Use three sections with `##` headings:

### Motivation

- State the problem and why now.
- Link related PRs, GitHub issues, or Jira tickets when they exist.
- Explain user/runner impact if the workflow behavior changes.

### Technical Details

- Describe the approach (not a file list dump).
- Note platform/arch scope, env vars, and what runs at prefetch vs per-test vs post-failure.
- Mention breaking changes or ops steps (secrets, `COMFYUI_PATH`, new assets).

### Submission Checklist

Copy checklist items from `.github/pull_request_template.md` and check off what was verified.

## Example skeleton

```markdown
## Motivation

Prior CI runs failed with HTTP 400 on LoadImage nodes because only model weights were prefetched, not `ComfyUI/input/` assets. Poll timeouts also masked ComfyUI server crashes.

## Technical Details

- Add bundled Comfy-Org template images under `assets/input/` and prefetch via `fetch_workflow_inputs.py`.
- Classify server crashes as `INFRA_ERROR` in `failure_classify.py`.
- Restart ComfyUI after non-PASS tests in `comfyui_benchmark.py`.

## Submission Checklist

- [ ] Look over the contributing guidelines at ...
- [ ] `python -m pytest tests/unit -q` passes
- [ ] ...
```

Do not use a bare bullet list without these three sections.
